Alan Rothwell is a British actor and television presenter . He first came to fame in 1960 , playing the character David Barlow in the soap opera Coronation Street . After leaving this role in 1968 , Alan became known as a presenter to a generation of children . He appeared on the children 's television programmes Picture Box from 1969 to 1990 and Hickory House from 1973 to 1978 . Alan returned to soap operas in 1985 , this time as heroin addict Nicholas Black in Brookside . Among his many other television credits are parts in Casualty , Emmerdale and Heartbeat . 